---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Our Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'leaving-lebanon', text: 'Leaving Lebanese Healthcare', level: 2 },
  { id: 'currency-crisis', text: 'Currency Crisis Impact', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Quick Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'popular-destinations', text: 'Popular Destinations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Best Gulf Region Insurance', href: '/best/gulf-region-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Europe Insurance', href: '/best/europe-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best US Coverage Insurance', href: '/best/us-coverage-insurance' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'arabicSupport', header: 'Arabic Support' },
  { key: 'gulfNetwork', header: 'Gulf Network' },
  { key: 'lebanonCoverage', header: 'Lebanon Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Starting Price' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', arabicSupport: 'Yes', gulfNetwork: 'Strong', lebanonCoverage: 'Add-on', price: '$175/mo' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', arabicSupport: 'Yes', gulfNetwork: 'Excellent', lebanonCoverage: 'Add-on', price: '$195/mo' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', arabicSupport: 'Limited', gulfNetwork: 'Strong', lebanonCoverage: 'Add-on', price: '$170/mo' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', arabicSupport: 'Yes', gulfNetwork: 'Strong', lebanonCoverage: 'Add-on', price: '$180/mo' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', arabicSupport: 'Limited', gulfNetwork: 'Excellent', lebanonCoverage: 'Included', price: '$165/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Health Insurance for Lebanese Expats 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance for Lebanese expats. Find USD-denominated coverage for Gulf countries, Europe, Americas, and Africa."
  headline="Best Insurance for Lebanese Expats in 2026"
  subheadline="Lebanon's diaspora is one of the world's largest relative to population. Here's how to stay protected with stable USD-denominated coverage."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/pages/lebanese-expat-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Cigna Quote →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Our Top Picks</h2>
  <p>
    Lebanese expats are spread across the Gulf, Americas, Europe, Africa, and Australia. Given Lebanon's currency situation, USD-denominated coverage is essential. Here's what we recommend:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Best overall for Lebanese expats. Strong Gulf networks, Arabic support, USD-denominated coverage.</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa Global:</strong> Premium option with excellent worldwide networks. Arabic support available.</li>
    <li><strong>AXA Global:</strong> Good global coverage with Arabic support. Strong presence in multiple regions.</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Good coverage at competitive prices.</li>
    <li><strong>Now Health:</strong> Strong Gulf and Asia presence with Lebanon coverage often included.</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="USD Coverage Essential"
    description="Given Lebanon's currency crisis, USD-denominated coverage is critical. Your policy limits maintain their value regardless of Lebanese pound movements. This protects your coverage purchasing power."
    buttonText="Get USD Coverage Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="leaving-lebanon">Leaving Lebanese Healthcare</h2>
  <p>
    Lebanon's healthcare system has been significantly impacted by the economic crisis. Here's what to know:
  </p>

  <h3>NSSF (National Social Security Fund)</h3>
  <p>
    NSSF provides healthcare coverage to formal sector employees in Lebanon. Coverage is tied to Lebanese employment and doesn't extend internationally. The system has faced funding challenges due to the economic crisis.
  </p>

  <h3>Private Lebanese Insurance</h3>
  <p>
    Private health insurance from Lebanese companies has been affected by the currency crisis. Policy values in Lebanese pounds have eroded significantly. International insurers with USD policies provide stable coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Public Healthcare</h3>
  <p>
    Lebanese public hospitals have faced severe challenges due to the economic situation. Many Lebanese have sought treatment abroad. International insurance facilitates access to quality healthcare outside Lebanon.
  </p>

  <h3>Medical Tourism Reversal</h3>
  <p>
    Lebanon was once a regional medical tourism destination. The situation has reversed—many Lebanese now travel abroad for treatment. International insurance supports this need.
  </p>

  <h2 id="currency-crisis">Currency Crisis Impact</h2>
  <p>
    Lebanon's currency crisis has major implications for health insurance:
  </p>

  <h3>Lebanese Pound Devaluation</h3>
  <p>
    The Lebanese pound has lost over 90% of its value. Insurance policies denominated in Lebanese pounds have effectively lost most of their coverage value. USD-denominated international insurance is essential.
  </p>

  <h3>USD-Denominated Benefits</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Coverage limits maintain actual purchasing power</li>
    <li>Claims paid at real international costs</li>
    <li>Premiums stable in hard currency terms</li>
    <li>Protection against further currency movements</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Payment Considerations</h3>
  <p>
    Paying premiums from Lebanon can be complicated by banking restrictions. Options include:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Payment from foreign income (easiest if earning abroad)</li>
    <li>International credit cards</li>
    <li>Fresh dollar accounts if available</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Arabic Language Support</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      Many Lebanese are multilingual (Arabic, French, English). Choose insurers with Arabic support for easier communication during medical situations. Cigna, Bupa, and AXA offer Arabic service through their Middle East operations.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Quick Comparison</h2>
  <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Cigna Global</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers comprehensive USD-denominated coverage ideal for Lebanese expats. Strong networks in the Gulf (large Lebanese diaspora), Americas, Europe, and Africa. Arabic support available through Middle East operations.
  </p>

  <p>
    Plans come in three tiers with coverage up to unlimited. Lebanon coverage can be added for visits home.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Lebanese expats who want reliable global coverage with Arabic support.
  </p>

  <h3>Bupa Global</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global offers premium international coverage with excellent worldwide networks. Arabic support available. Service quality is outstanding with comprehensive benefits.
  </p>

  <p>
    Higher pricing reflects premium quality. Best for professionals who can afford top-tier coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Lebanese professionals who want the best coverage available.
  </p>

  <h3>AXA Global</h3>
  <p>
    AXA has presence in the Middle East and globally. Good coverage with Arabic support. Strong networks in multiple regions where Lebanese diaspora is concentrated.
  </p>

  <p>
    Good option for those who want regional understanding with global coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Lebanese expats who want good global coverage with regional expertise.
  </p>

  <h3>Allianz Care</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers good global coverage at competitive prices. Strong networks in Europe (significant Lebanese diaspora) and adequate coverage elsewhere.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Lebanese expats seeking good value with global coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Now Health</h3>
  <p>
    Now Health has strong Gulf and Asian presence. Lebanon coverage is often included automatically. Good option for Gulf-based Lebanese expats.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Lebanese expats in Gulf who want included Lebanon coverage.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Your Options"
    description="Get USD-denominated quotes from multiple providers. Compare networks in your destination region and Arabic support availability."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna-global"
  />

  <h2 id="popular-destinations">Popular Destinations</h2>
  <p>
    Lebanese diaspora is global. Here's what to consider by region:
  </p>

  <h3>Gulf Countries (UAE, Saudi, Kuwait, Qatar)</h3>
  <p>
    Large Lebanese professional community. Employer-provided insurance is common but quality varies. Many Lebanese doctors practice in the Gulf. Supplemental coverage ensures comprehensive protection.
  </p>

  <h3>Europe (France, Germany, UK)</h3>
  <p>
    Historical ties with France. EU countries have public healthcare for legal residents. Private insurance supplements public access. Paris has a significant Lebanese community.
  </p>

  <h3>Americas (Brazil, US, Canada, Mexico)</h3>
  <p>
    Largest Lebanese diaspora concentrations globally, especially Brazil. US healthcare requires comprehensive coverage. Canada and Brazil have public systems for residents.
  </p>

  <h3>West Africa (Senegal, Côte d'Ivoire, Nigeria)</h3>
  <p>
    Historic Lebanese trading communities. Healthcare infrastructure varies—international insurance ensures access to quality care and evacuation if needed.
  </p>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is Lebanese insurance still valid?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Lebanese pound-denominated policies have lost most value due to currency devaluation. USD-denominated international insurance is essential for real coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">How do I pay from Lebanon?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Banking restrictions complicate payments. Pay from foreign income, use international cards, or fresh dollar accounts if available.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Should I get USD or EUR coverage?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">USD is most common and recommended. Both provide stability against Lebanese pound devaluation. Choose based on your destination's currency.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What about coverage during Lebanon visits?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Most international insurers offer Lebanon as a coverage region. Given healthcare challenges in Lebanon, international insurance provides options including evacuation.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is Arabic support important?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Many Lebanese speak multiple languages, but Arabic support can help during stressful medical situations. Cigna, Bupa, and AXA offer Arabic service.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What about medical evacuation?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Given healthcare challenges in some destinations, evacuation coverage is important. All recommended insurers include evacuation benefits.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Final Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    Lebanese expats need USD-denominated international insurance—Lebanese pound coverage has lost value. <strong>Cigna Global</strong> is our top recommendation for reliable coverage with Arabic support and global networks.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Bupa Global</strong> offers premium coverage for those who can afford the best. <strong>AXA Global</strong> provides good regional expertise. <strong>Now Health</strong> suits Gulf-based expats who want included Lebanon coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    Don't rely on Lebanese insurance given the currency situation. USD-denominated coverage from international insurers provides real protection regardless of economic conditions.
  </p>

</PageShell>
